The paper introduces a new dimensionality reduction technique that outperforms existing methods on a variety of datasets in terms of quality and runtime. This makes it relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural networks (cs.NE).
